<div id="bodycontent">
  <h2>Quotes</h2>
  <p><img src="Wirth.jpg"
     alt="Niklaus Wirth"
     width="300" height="200"/></p>
	 <p style="font-style: italic">Software slows down faster than hardware speeds up.- <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wirth%27s_law">Wirth's Law</a></p>
     <p>This quote became later to be known as Wirth's Law. 
     It means that no matter how fast our hardware 
	 becomes, the software will find a way through bloat
	 and complexity to slow it down.</p>
  <p style="font-style: italic">In our profession, precision and perfection are not
     a dispensable luxury, but a simple necessity. -<a href="http://www.eptacom.net/pubblicazioni/pub_eng/wirth.html">A Few Words with Niklaus Wirth</a></p>
  <p>This is a straight forward statement about the 
     importance of clean programming. It must be concise
	 a readable from the start.</p>
  <p style="font-style: italic">Reliable and transparent programs are usually not in the interest of the designer.- <a href="http://www.modulaware.com/mdlt/mdlt79.htm">
     A Digital Contrarian Retires</a></p>
  <p>Niklaus is saying that designer seek out problems to solve and improve.</p>
